    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7434" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέπων</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ονος</span>, voc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέπον</span>
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέσσω</span>): cooked by the sun,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ripe, mellow;</span> in Homer only fig., (1) as term of
          endearment, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">dear, pet</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            6.35</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 17.120</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.447</span></i>.—(2) in bad sense,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">coward, weakling</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            2.235</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          13.120</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
